headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 32 points and nine rebounds, Jalen Duren added 12 points and 19 rebounds, and the Detroit Pistons won their seventh straight game with a 106-97 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham and Duren lead Pistons to 7th straight win with 106-97 victory over Clippers

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had a career-best 19 assists, while adding 18 points and nine rebounds, Aaron Gordon scored 25 points and the Denver Nuggets defeated the Indiana Pacers 125-116 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aaron Gordon, Nikola Jokic lead Nuggets past Pacers 125-116

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey had 25 points, 16 rebounds and six assists as the Chicago Bulls ended a six-game skid by routing the Philadelphia 76ers 142-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giddey scores 25 points as the Bulls snap a 6-game skid with a 142-110 rout of the 76ers

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 26 points, including a couple of crucial jumpers late as the Washington Wizards snapped their six-game losing streak with a 107-99 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 26 as the Wizards snap their 6-game losing streak with a 107-99 victory over the Nets

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 11 points and 14 assists, and the Atlanta Hawks snapped a three-game losing streak with a 98-86 victory over the Miami Heat on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks allow their fewest points in nearly 4 years, shut down Heat 98-86

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jaden McDaniels scored 27 points, Anthony Edwards blocked Shai Gilgeous-Alexander's go-ahead shot attempt and the Minnesota Timberwolves overcame a 25-point deficit in the second half to beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 131-128 in overtime on Monday...
headlines.shortLinkText: McDaniels scores 27, and Timberwolves rally from 25-point deficit to beat Thunder 131-128 in OT

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons had 28 points and out six assists to lead the Portland Trail Blazers to a 114-112 victory over the Utah Jazz on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anfernee Simons scores 28, Trail Blazers beat Jazz 114-112 in opener of a 7-game trip

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored a season-high 42 points in his finest game with Sacramento since being acquired in a multi-team trade near the deadline, leading the Kings to a 130-88 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine scores season-high 42 points to help Kings beat Hornets 130-88
